\title{Equivalence Relation}
\taxon{Definition}
\p{
    An equivalence relation #{R} on a set #{A} is a [relation](def-000W) that is reflexive,
    symmetric, and transitive.
    \ul{
        \li{Reflexive:
            #{\forall x\in A, xRx}
        }
        \li{Symmetric:
            #{\forall x,y\in A, xRy\implies yRx}
        }
        \li{Transitive:
            #{\forall x,y,z\in A, xRy\land yRz\implies xRz}
        }
    }
    We often denote the equivalence relation by #{\sim}.
}